#. HTML: <section class="sutta" id="mn134"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "mn134:0.1"
msgid "Majjhima Nikāya 134 "
msgstr "Middle Discourses 134 "

#. HTML: </p><h1>
msgctxt "mn134:0.2"
msgid "Lomasakaṅgiyabhaddekarattasutta "
msgstr "Lomasakaṅgiya and One Fine Night "

#. HTML: </h1></div><p><span class="evam">
#. REF: nya1, pts-vp-pli3.200, sc1
msgctxt "mn134:1.1"
msgid "Evaṃ me sutaṃ—"
msgstr "So I have heard. "

#. HTML: </span>
msgctxt "mn134:1.2"
msgid "ekaṃ samayaṃ bhagavā sāvatthiyaṃ viharati jetavane anāthapiṇḍikassa ārāme. "
msgstr "At one time the Buddha was staying near Sāvatthī in Jeta’s Grove, Anāthapiṇḍika’s monastery. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. VAR: lomasakaṅgiyo → lomasaka­kaṅ­giyo (ṭīkā)
msgctxt "mn134:1.3"
msgid "Tena kho pana samayena āyasmā lomasakaṅgiyo sakkesu viharati kapilavatthusmiṃ nigrodhārāme. "
msgstr "Now at that time Venerable Lomasakaṅgiya was staying in the Sakyan country at Kapilavatthu in the Banyan Tree Monastery. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: nya2
msgctxt "mn134:2.1"
msgid "Atha kho candano devaputto abhikkantāya rattiyā abhikkantavaṇṇo kevalakappaṃ nigrodhārāmaṃ obhāsetvā yenāyasmā lomasakaṅgiyo tenupasaṅkami; upasaṅkamitvā ekamantaṃ aṭṭhāsi. Ekamantaṃ ṭhito kho candano devaputto āyasmantaṃ lomasakaṅgiyaṃ etadavoca: "
msgstr "Then, late at night, the glorious god Candana, lighting up the entire Banyan Tree Monastery, went up to the Venerable Lomasakaṅgiya, and stood to one side. Standing to one side, he said to Lomasakaṅgiya: "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "mn134:2.2"
msgid "“dhāresi tvaṃ, bhikkhu, bhaddekarattassa uddesañca vibhaṅgañcā”ti? "
msgstr "“Mendicant, do you remember the recitation passage and analysis of One Fine Night?” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "mn134:2.3"
msgid "“Na kho ahaṃ, āvuso, dhāremi bhaddekarattassa uddesañca vibhaṅgañca. "
msgstr "“No, reverend, I do not. "

msgctxt "mn134:2.4"
msgid "Tvaṃ panāvuso, dhāresi bhaddekarattassa uddesañca vibhaṅgañcā”ti? "
msgstr "Do you?” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "mn134:2.5"
msgid "“Ahampi kho, bhikkhu, na dhāremi bhaddekarattassa uddesañca vibhaṅgañca. "
msgstr "“I also do not. "

msgctxt "mn134:2.6"
msgid "Dhāresi pana tvaṃ, bhikkhu, bhaddekarattiyo gāthā”ti? "
msgstr "But do you remember just the verses on One Fine Night?” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "mn134:2.7"
msgid "“Na kho ahaṃ, āvuso, dhāremi bhaddekarattiyo gāthā. "
msgstr "“I do not. "

msgctxt "mn134:2.8"
msgid "Tvaṃ panāvuso, dhāresi bhaddekarattiyo gāthā”ti? "
msgstr "Do you?” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "mn134:2.9"
msgid "“Dhāremi kho ahaṃ, bhikkhu, bhaddekarattiyo gāthā”ti. "
msgstr "“I do.” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "mn134:2.10"
msgid "“Yathā kathaṃ pana tvaṃ, āvuso, dhāresi bhaddekarattiyo gāthā”ti? "
msgstr "“How do you remember the verses on One Fine Night?” "

# NOTE: pandukambala is regularly given in the list of luxury upholserty.
#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "mn134:2.11"
msgid "“Ekamidaṃ, bhikkhu, samayaṃ bhagavā devesu tāvatiṃsesu viharati pāricchattakamūle paṇḍukambalasilāyaṃ. "
msgstr "“This one time, the Buddha was staying among the gods of the Thirty-Three at the root of the Shady Orchard Tree on the stone spread with a cream rug. "

msgctxt "mn134:2.12"
msgid "Tatra bhagavā devānaṃ tāvatiṃsānaṃ bhaddekarattassa uddesañca vibhaṅgañca abhāsi: "
msgstr "There he taught the recitation passage and analysis of One Fine Night to the gods of the Thirty-Three: "

#. HTML: </p><blockquote class="gatha"><p>
#. REF: nya3, sc2
msgctxt "mn134:3.1"
msgid "‘Atītaṃ nānvāgameyya, "
msgstr "‘Don’t run back to the past, "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "mn134:3.2"
msgid "nappaṭikaṅkhe anāgataṃ; "
msgstr "don’t hope for the future. "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "mn134:3.3"
msgid "Yadatītaṃ pahīnaṃ taṃ, "
msgstr "What’s past is left behind; "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "mn134:3.4"
msgid "appattañca anāgataṃ. "
msgstr "the future has not arrived; "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc3
msgctxt "mn134:3.5"
msgid "Paccuppannañca yo dhammaṃ, "
msgstr "and phenomena in the present "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "mn134:3.6"
msgid "tattha tattha vipassati; "
msgstr "are clearly seen in every case. "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "mn134:3.7"
msgid "Asaṃhīraṃ asaṅkuppaṃ, "
msgstr "Knowing this, foster it—"

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "mn134:3.8"
msgid "taṃ vidvā manubrūhaye. "
msgstr "unfaltering, unshakable. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc4
msgctxt "mn134:3.9"
msgid "Ajjeva kiccamātappaṃ, "
msgstr "Today’s the day to keenly work—"

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "mn134:3.10"
msgid "ko jaññā maraṇaṃ suve; "
msgstr "who knows, tomorrow may bring death! "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "mn134:3.11"
msgid "Na hi no saṅgaraṃ tena, "
msgstr "For there is no bargain to be struck "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "mn134:3.12"
msgid "mahāsenena maccunā. "
msgstr "with Death and his mighty hordes. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc5
msgctxt "mn134:3.13"
msgid "Evaṃvihāriṃ ātāpiṃ, "
msgstr "The peaceful sage explained it’s those "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "mn134:3.14"
msgid "ahorattamatanditaṃ; "
msgstr "who keenly meditate like this, "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "mn134:3.15"
msgid "Taṃ ve bhaddekarattoti, "
msgstr "tireless all night and day, "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "mn134:3.16"
msgid "santo ācikkhate munī’ti. "
msgstr "who truly have that one fine night.’ "

#. HTML: </p></blockquote><p>
#. REF: nya4, sc6
msgctxt "mn134:4.1"
msgid "Evaṃ kho ahaṃ, bhikkhu, dhāremi bhaddekarattiyo gāthā. "
msgstr "That’s how I remember the verses of One Fine Night. "

msgctxt "mn134:4.2"
msgid "Uggaṇhāhi tvaṃ, bhikkhu, bhaddekarattassa uddesañca vibhaṅgañca; "
msgstr "Learn the recitation passage and analysis of One Fine Night, mendicant, "

msgctxt "mn134:4.3"
msgid "pariyāpuṇāhi tvaṃ, bhikkhu, bhaddekarattassa uddesañca vibhaṅgañca; "
msgstr "memorize it, "

msgctxt "mn134:4.4"
msgid "dhārehi tvaṃ, bhikkhu, bhaddekarattassa uddesañca vibhaṅgañca. "
msgstr "and remember it. "

msgctxt "mn134:4.5"
msgid "Atthasaṃhito, bhikkhu, bhaddekarattassa uddeso ca vibhaṅgo ca ādibrahmacariyako”ti. "
msgstr "It is beneficial and relates to the fundamentals of the spiritual life.” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "mn134:4.6"
msgid "Idamavoca candano devaputto. "
msgstr "That’s what the god Candana said "

msgctxt "mn134:4.7"
msgid "Idaṃ vatvā tatthevantaradhāyi. "
msgstr "before vanishing right there. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: nya5, pts-vp-pli3.201, sc7
msgctxt "mn134:5.1"
msgid "Atha kho āyasmā lomasakaṅgiyo tassā rattiyā accayena senāsanaṃ saṃsāmetvā pattacīvaramādāya yena sāvatthi tena cārikaṃ pakkāmi. "
msgstr "Then Lomasakaṅgiya set his lodgings in order and, taking his bowl and robe, set out for Sāvatthī. "

msgctxt "mn134:5.2"
msgid "Anupubbena cārikaṃ caramāno yena sāvatthi jetavanaṃ anāthapiṇḍikassa ārāmo yena bhagavā tenupasaṅkami; upasaṅkamitvā bhagavantaṃ abhivādetvā ekamantaṃ nisīdi. Ekamantaṃ nisinno kho āyasmā lomasakaṅgiyo bhagavantaṃ etadavoca: "
msgstr "Eventually he came to Sāvatthī and Jeta’s Grove. He went up to the Buddha, bowed, sat down to one side, and told him what had happened. Then he added: "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc8
msgctxt "mn134:5.3"
msgid "“Ekamidāhaṃ, bhante, samayaṃ sakkesu viharāmi kapilavatthusmiṃ nigrodhārāme. "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "mn134:5.4"
msgid "Atha kho, bhante, aññataro devaputto abhikkantāya rattiyā abhikkantavaṇṇo kevalakappaṃ nigrodhārāmaṃ obhāsetvā yenāhaṃ tenupasaṅkami; upasaṅkamitvā ekamantaṃ aṭṭhāsi. Ekamantaṃ ṭhito kho, bhante, so devaputto maṃ etadavoca: "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "mn134:5.5"
msgid "‘dhāresi tvaṃ, bhikkhu, bhaddekarattassa uddesañca vibhaṅgañcā’ti? "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "mn134:5.6"
msgid "Evaṃ vutte, ahaṃ, bhante, taṃ devaputtaṃ etadavocaṃ: "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "mn134:5.7"
msgid "‘na kho ahaṃ, āvuso, dhāremi bhaddekarattassa uddesañca vibhaṅgañca. "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "mn134:5.8"
msgid "Tvaṃ panāvuso, dhāresi bhaddekarattassa uddesañca vibhaṅgañcā’ti? "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "mn134:5.9"
msgid "‘Ahampi kho, bhikkhu, na dhāremi bhaddekarattassa uddesañca vibhaṅgañca. "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "mn134:5.10"
msgid "Dhāresi pana tvaṃ, bhikkhu, bhaddekarattiyo gāthā’ti? "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "mn134:5.11"
msgid "‘Na kho ahaṃ, āvuso, dhāremi bhaddekarattiyo gāthā. "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "mn134:5.12"
msgid "Tvaṃ panāvuso, dhāresi bhaddekarattiyo gāthā’ti? "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "mn134:5.13"
msgid "‘Dhāremi kho ahaṃ, bhikkhu, bhaddekarattiyo gāthā’ti. "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "mn134:5.14"
msgid "‘Yathā kathaṃ pana tvaṃ, āvuso, dhāresi bhaddekarattiyo gāthā’ti? "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "mn134:5.15"
msgid "‘Ekamidaṃ, bhikkhu, samayaṃ bhagavā devesu tāvatiṃsesu viharati pāricchattakamūle paṇḍukambalasilāyaṃ. "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "mn134:5.16"
msgid "Tatra kho bhagavā devānaṃ tāvatiṃsānaṃ bhaddekarattassa uddesañca vibhaṅgañca abhāsi: "
msgstr " "

#. HTML: </p><blockquote class="gatha"><p>
#. REF: sc9
msgctxt "mn134:5.17"
msgid "“Atītaṃ nānvāgameyya, "
msgstr " "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "mn134:5.18"
msgid "… pe … "
msgstr " "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "mn134:5.19"
msgid "Taṃ ve bhaddekarattoti, "
msgstr " "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "mn134:5.20"
msgid "santo ācikkhate munī”ti. "
msgstr " "

#. HTML: </p></blockquote><p>
#. REF: sc10
msgctxt "mn134:5.21"
msgid "Evaṃ kho ahaṃ, bhikkhu, dhāremi bhaddekarattiyo gāthā. "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "mn134:5.22"
msgid "Uggaṇhāhi tvaṃ, bhikkhu, bhaddekarattassa uddesañca vibhaṅgañca; "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "mn134:5.23"
msgid "pariyāpuṇāhi tvaṃ, bhikkhu, bhaddekarattassa uddesañca vibhaṅgañca; "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "mn134:5.24"
msgid "dhārehi tvaṃ, bhikkhu, bhaddekarattassa uddesañca vibhaṅgañca. "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "mn134:5.25"
msgid "Atthasaṃhito, bhikkhu, bhaddekarattassa uddeso ca vibhaṅgo ca ādibrahmacariyako’ti. "
msgstr " "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "mn134:5.26"
msgid "Idamavoca, bhante, so devaputto. "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "mn134:5.27"
msgid "Idaṃ vatvā tatthevantaradhāyi. "
msgstr " "

msgctxt "mn134:5.28"
msgid "Sādhu me, bhante, bhagavā bhaddekarattassa uddesañca vibhaṅgañca desetū”ti. "
msgstr "“Sir, please teach me the recitation passage and analysis of One Fine night.” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: nya6, sc11
msgctxt "mn134:6.1"
msgid "“Jānāsi pana tvaṃ, bhikkhu, taṃ devaputtan”ti? "
msgstr "“But mendicant, do you know that god?” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "mn134:6.2"
msgid "“Na kho ahaṃ, bhante, jānāmi taṃ devaputtan”ti. "
msgstr "“I do not, sir.” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "mn134:6.3"
msgid "“Candano nāma so, bhikkhu, devaputto. "
msgstr "“That god was named Candana. "

#. VAR: aṭṭhiṃ katvā → aṭṭhikatvā (bj, s1-3, km, pts1)
#. VAR: sabbacetasā → sabbacetaso (bj) | sabbaṃ cetaso (si, s1-3, km, pts1) | sabbaṃ cetasā (mr)
msgctxt "mn134:6.4"
msgid "Candano, bhikkhu, devaputto aṭṭhiṃ katvā manasikatvā sabbacetasā samannāharitvā ohitasoto dhammaṃ suṇāti. "
msgstr "Candana pays heed, pays attention, engages wholeheartedly, and lends an ear to the teaching. "

msgctxt "mn134:6.5"
msgid "Tena hi, bhikkhu, suṇāhi, sādhukaṃ manasi karohi; bhāsissāmī”ti. "
msgstr "Well then, mendicant, listen and pay close attention, I will speak.” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "mn134:6.6"
msgid "“Evaṃ, bhante”ti kho āyasmā lomasakaṅgiyo bhagavato paccassosi. "
msgstr "“Yes, sir,” Lomasakaṅgiya replied. "

msgctxt "mn134:6.7"
msgid "Bhagavā etadavoca: "
msgstr "The Buddha said this: "

